Fractal abstract events: compiler pipeline as self-similar pattern

Design:
- WHOLE pipeline is ~abstract event compiler.coordinate
- EACH step is ~abstract event compiler.{parse,analyze,transform,optimize,emit}
- Same pattern at every level (fractal/self-similar)
- Users override at ANY level via ~impl

Capabilities:
- Replace whole pipeline OR individual steps
- Wrap steps (delegate to default, add before/after logic)
- Compose default + custom steps freely
- All compile-time resolved, zero runtime overhead

Integration with today's features:
- Event globbing: ~abstract event transform.* for families
- AI integration: inject ai_explain as a step
- Pruning: steps can short-circuit via .pruned

This is the endgame: user-controllable compiler as pure Koru code.
